MGI-to-Ensembl gene identifier mappings

Source: R/AllClasses.R, R/MGI2Ensembl.R
MGI2Ensembl-class.Rd

MGI-to-Ensembl gene identifier mappings

MGI2Ensembl()

Value

MGI2Ensembl. Contains a DataFrame with mgiID and geneID columns.

Note

Updated 2019-07-28.

Examples

options(acid.test = TRUE)
x <- MGI2Ensembl()
#> Obtaining MGI to Ensembl gene ID mappings.
print(x)
#> MGI2Ensembl with 10 rows and 2 columns
#>        mgiID             geneID
#>    <integer>        <character>
#> 1     103039 ENSMUSG00000040033
#> 2     106222 ENSMUSG00000015733
#> 3    1261811 ENSMUSG00000042678
#> 4    1914751 ENSMUSG00000038127
#> 5    1915395 ENSMUSG00000016984
#> 6    1916421 ENSMUSG00000033159
#> 7    3031196 ENSMUSG00000051258
#> 8    3040677 ENSMUSG00000039108
#> 9    3648770 ENSMUSG00000086158
#> 10   3761311 ENSMUSG00000091006
